-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Fibria, Itau Unibanco, MRV Engenharia
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2011-12-27T20:44:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/brazilian-stock-movers-fibria-itau-unibanco-mrv-engenharia.html
The following companies had  unusual (IBOV) 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 0.6 percent to 58,005.20.  Fibria Celulose SA  (FIBR3 BS) gained 1 percent to 14.44
reais. Investors are optimistic on the outlook for the world’s
largest pulp producer because declining inventories signal
prices may rebound, said Marcos Assumpcao, an analyst at Itau
Corretora de Valores SA.  Itau Unibanco Holdings SA  (ITUB4 BS) added 0.2 percent to
34.31 reais.  Latin America ’s largest bank is selling its
Orbitall credit- and debit-card processing unit to a Brazilian
software producer, according to two people familiar with the
transaction who asked not to be identified because the deal
hasn’t been announced. Officials from Itau declined to comment.  Homebuilders gained as investors bet the central bank will
keep lowering borrowing costs to spur economic growth.  MRV
Engenharia & Participacoes SA  (MRVE3 BS),  Brazil ’s fifth-biggest
homebuilder by revenue, rallied 2.2 percent to 11.15 reais as
yields on the interest-rate futures contract due January 2013
fell eight basis points, or 0.08 percentage point, to 10.1
percent. Rival  Rossi Residencial SA  (RSID3 BS) fell 1.1 percent
to 8.40 reais, after earlier gaining as much as 2.1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
